Compiling:
    A Makefile is provided, type make/make all in order to
    compile the TCPserver.c and TCPclient.c programs.
    TCPserver.c -> server
    TCPclient.c -> client

Running server:
    In order to run server you must type:
    ./server [port-number]

    The port I am assigned is 12016, so:
    ./server 12016

Running client:
    In order to run client you must type:
    ./client [ip-address:port-number] [chunk-size] [file-path]

    Please note the [chunk-size] parameter is optional. The
    program will default to chunk sizes of 4096 bytes.

Reasoning behind file-naming convention:
    If a duplicate file is found in the same directory, an
    underscore and a number will be appended to the end of
    the filename.

    For example:

        Duplicate cat.txt
        cat_(#).txt

Running script:
    In order to run the script you must type:
    bash multi_client.bash

    This will open 5 xterm terminals, execute the ./client
    command with wonderland.txt and then close the 5 xterm
    terminals, printing the output to the parent terminal.

Cleaning up:
    In order to clean up the directory simply type:
    make clean

